# Mashup Generation — Prompt Templates

These are ready-to-use prompts you can paste into Cursor Chat to generate a mashup.
Copy, fill in the `< >` placeholders, and send.

---

## PROMPT 1 — Create a Brand-New Mashup Project

```
Create a new Odin mashup project called <project-name>.

Steps:
1. In the terminal, navigate to the Projects folder:
   cd "Mashup Manager/Projects"
2. Run `odin new`.
3. When asked for the project name, enter: <project-name>
4. When asked to select a library, choose: soho
5. After generation, cd into the project and run `npm install`.

The mashup should:
- <Describe the main purpose — e.g. "display a list of customers with filtering and the ability to open a detail form">
- Use the following IDS components:
    - <List components, e.g. soho-datagrid for the main list>
    - <e.g. soho-modal-dialog for the detail form>
    - <e.g. soho-toolbar-flex for the page header>
- Data comes from: <describe the data source — e.g. "a mock array of customer objects" or "a REST endpoint at /api/customers">

Before writing any component, read:
  - Mashup Manager/Components Library/ids-enterprise-ng/lib/<component>/*.component.d.ts
  - Mashup Manager/Components Library/scraped_components/<slug>/example-index_html/page.html

Follow all rules in .cursor/rules/.
```

