## PROMPT 2 — Add a Single IDS Component to an Existing Mashup

```
Add a <component-name> component to the mashup at <path-to-component-folder>.

Requirements:
- <Describe what this component should do — e.g. "show a paginated, sortable data grid of orders">
- Inputs: <list the data properties the component will receive as @Input>
- Outputs: <list the events the component should emit as @Output>

Before generating the code:
1. Read: Mashup Manager/Components Library/ids-enterprise-ng/lib/<ids-component>/soho-<ids-component>.component.d.ts
2. Read: Mashup Manager/Components Library/scraped_components/<slug>/example-index_html/page.html

Use only documented @Input/@Output names from the .d.ts file.
Follow all coding rules in .cursor/rules/mashup-coding-rules.mdc.
```

---

## PROMPT 3 — Generate a Full Feature Page (List + Detail)

```
Generate a full feature page for <feature-name> in the existing mashup at <project-path>.

The page should have:
1. A toolbar (soho-toolbar-flex) with:
   - A page title: "<Page Title>"
   - An "Add New" primary button
   - A search field

2. A data grid (soho-datagrid) that:
   - Shows columns: <list column names and field paths>
   - Supports single-row selection
   - Emits (rowActivated) to open the detail panel

3. A modal dialog (soho-modal-dialog) that:
   - Opens when a row is activated or "Add New" is clicked
   - Contains a form with: <list form fields and their IDS component types>
   - Has Save and Cancel buttons

Data model (TypeScript interface):
<paste or describe the model, e.g.:
interface Order {
  id: number;
  customerName: string;
  status: 'open' | 'closed' | 'pending';
  orderDate: Date;
}
>

Data source: <mock array / HTTP service at /api/<endpoint>>

Rules:
- Consult the component library for every IDS component used.
- Follow .cursor/rules/mashup-coding-rules.mdc for all TypeScript and Angular conventions.
- Follow .cursor/rules/odin-framework.mdc for project-specific conventions.
```

